The earlier I-D were only checking that the two endpoint-id were different and this is no longer needed since the endpoint-id is a key:

```
      leaf id {
        type string;
        must '. != ../../endpoint-1/id' {
          error-message
            "The two end points must not be equal to each other. ";
        }
        mandatory true;
        description
          "Subscriber end point ID of the other end";
      }
```

Note that the must statement in -19 was wrong ('id' should have been changed to 'endpoint-id' and not to 'uni'.

There has never been a check that the two reference UNIs are different.

See: https://mailarchive.ietf.org/arch/msg/ccamp/tcm3z89Tj4fd_kq28e5GicfvmAo/

